SIMPLE: indubitate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indubitate
<hw>In*du"bi*tate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>indubitatus</ets>; pref. <ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>dubitatus</ets>,
p. p. of <ets>dubitare</ets> to doubt.]</ety> <def>Not questioned or
doubtful; evident; certain.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indubitate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Indubitate
<hw>In*du"bi*tate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>indubitatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>indubitare</ets>; pref.
<ets>in-</ets> in + <ets>dubitare</ets> to doubt.]</ety> <def>To bring
into doubt; to cause to be doubted.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To conceal, or <qex>indubitate</qex>, his exigency.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir T. Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Induce</ent>⟦br⟧
